<span id="freeTextContainer6446186644571682712"><b>It&apos;s hard not to ask yourself what life is all about and whether there&apos;s any sense to it or whether it&apos;s all a tragic blunder of blind fate</b><br/><br/>I was sitting at my aunt and uncle&apos;s house with nothing to do except watch the Hallmark channel which I loathe beyond words. I looked in my uncle&apos;s library and selected a book at random and this was the book. From page one I was riveted but unfortunately I couldn&apos;t take the book with me so I bought my own copy and I&apos;m so glad I did. The novel centers around L</span>
  <span id="freeText6446186644571682712" style="display:none"><b>It's hard not to ask yourself what life is all about and whether there's any sense to it or whether it's all a tragic blunder of blind fate</b><br /><br />I was sitting at my aunt and uncle's house with nothing to do except watch the Hallmark channel which I loathe beyond words. I looked in my uncle's library and selected a book at random and this was the book. From page one I was riveted but unfortunately I couldn't take the book with me so I bought my own copy and I'm so glad I did. The novel centers around Larry, a man who leaves behind his bourgeois lifestyle to live a life of spiritual fulfillment. This novel spoke to in ways that I wish all novel would do. Every line of every page compelled me to read it and it's been quite a while since a novel has done that for me. 5 out 5.<br /><br /><b>Unfortunately sometimes one can't do what one thinks is right without making someone else unhappy.</b></span>
