  <span id="freeText5060474902648436754" style="display:none">It took me a long time to read this book, this beautiful book, this excellent book. I took time because every sentence, every word deserves to be read carefully. It indeed served by subtle prose, sought after in its simplicity.<br />The stories are complete. They demonstrate how each life carries a greater or lesser share of tragedy and ridicule; how happiness cannot be an exact science. It is even happy that each has its definition: it can hide in futility like the Absolute. They also allow you to position yourself facing each of the characters described in this beautiful book, this lovely book.</span>
