<div id="review_1209077004" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1209077004" />
    <a title="Stacia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3917029-stacia"><img alt="Stacia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1316011190p2/3917029.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1209077004?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacia" href="/user/show/3917029-stacia">Stacia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140185232" href="/book/show/117834.The_Razor_s_Edge">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3917029-stacia?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3917029-stacia?shelf=europe">europe</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3917029-stacia?shelf=2015">2015</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3917029-stacia?shelf=2017">2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1209077004" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7958189513485345058">What a keen observer of people Maugham is! This book is just a wonderful delight, amusing &amp; serious at the same time, filled with Maugham&apos;s warm, wonderful observations of people. <br/><br/>It&apos;s like visiting a bunch of old friends various times throughout the years, telling stories, catching up on gossip, pondering the meaning of life, etc.... Maugham writes beautifully. All the characters are great -- true people with many virtues, but flaws too; the flaws don&apos;t detract, though, just make them real. (El</span>
  <span id="freeText7958189513485345058" style="display:none">What a keen observer of people Maugham is! This book is just a wonderful delight, amusing &amp; serious at the same time, filled with Maugham's warm, wonderful observations of people. <br /><br />It's like visiting a bunch of old friends various times throughout the years, telling stories, catching up on gossip, pondering the meaning of life, etc.... Maugham writes beautifully. All the characters are great -- true people with many virtues, but flaws too; the flaws don't detract, though, just make them real. (Elliott becomes the center of attention in every scene he graces! Loved him, lol!) <br /><br />As the book closes, Maugham writes,<br /><blockquote>"But as I was finishing this book, uneasily conscious that I must leave my reader in the air and seeing no way to avoid it, I looked back with my mind's eye on my long narrative to see if there was any way in which I could devise a more satisfactory ending; and to my intense surprise it dawned upon me that without the least intending to I had written nothing more or less than a success story."</blockquote><br />Unlike so many books with "big" events or sad or shocking events used as literary devices, this one is similar to life with a warmth &amp; love of humanity that infuses the characters with more good than bad, events with overall hope, and a pleasant ending. (That doesn't mean there aren't sad events, but those are seen as a part of a normal life where family &amp; friends help one get through &amp; still enjoy life.) By my reckoning, The Razor's Edge is a modern classic &amp; a 5-star book.<br />------------------------<br />Addendum 2017: Just started this book again. What a treat to be meeting all the characters again!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7958189513485345058" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
