<span id="freeTextContainer4058195990094956209">I liked it! As for writing a review ---there are a TON of EXCELLENT reveiws already written ---<br/>[which I&apos;ve enjoyed very much myself....as many of them expanded my own understanding -and views of this book]....<br/><br/>One little thing which &apos;bugged&apos; me personally ----lol ---is that &apos;LEGS&apos; on woman seemed to be a first physical focus (fat -or thin -short or tall) ---<br/><br/>As a female ---I was a little &apos;tired&apos; of the LEG talk....<br/><br/>Larry spent 2 years in an Ashram ----(I spent a week and had enough) ---<br/>A VERY close</span>
  <span id="freeText4058195990094956209" style="display:none">I liked it! As for writing a review ---there are a TON of EXCELLENT reveiws already written ---<br />[which I've enjoyed very much myself....as many of them expanded my own understanding -and views of this book]....<br /><br />One little thing which 'bugged' me personally ----lol ---is that 'LEGS' on woman seemed to be a first physical focus (fat -or thin -short or tall) ---<br /><br />As a female ---I was a little 'tired' of the LEG talk....<br /><br />Larry spent 2 years in an Ashram ----(I spent a week and had enough) ---<br />A VERY close friend and professional international singer grew up in an Ashram ---(OH MY ---'HER' book would knock your socks off)....'free' love' in front of children...etc.<br /><br />Anyway ---I enjoyed the book ---YES its at least worth 4 stars ----but at times I was thinking I might have enjoyed this book better in 1970. <br /><br />Remember ---I live in the Bay Area ---(grew up in Berkeley) ---NOT too much about this book will change my life. Yet ---I found it fascinating to read OTHER reviews (written years ago??) in which people thought this was the MOST important book they had ever read... hm????<br /><br />Maybe I'm just an old fart!<br /><br />but.........Its GOOD ---no question : Beautiful writing!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4058195990094956209" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


