    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4457054106" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4457054106" />
    <a title="Janelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle"><img alt="Janelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581393896p2/88713906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4457054106?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janelle" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle">Janelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781407016542" href="/book/show/17425793-the-razor-s-edge">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=2022">2022</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4457054106" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3366736174013211069">The story of Larry Durrell is told to the author, by Larry himself, and friends. Maugham is the narrator and it’s an unusual way to write the book but it worked for me. I found it very engaging. In some ways I was reminded of Gatsby. Many characters are just materialistic, and superficial. (I really didn’t like Isabel, she got more and more on my nerves as the book went on!) After being a pilot in the First World War, Larry returns home but is no longer interested in getting a job and settling d</span>
  <span id="freeText3366736174013211069" style="display:none">The story of Larry Durrell is told to the author, by Larry himself, and friends. Maugham is the narrator and it’s an unusual way to write the book but it worked for me. I found it very engaging. In some ways I was reminded of Gatsby. Many characters are just materialistic, and superficial. (I really didn’t like Isabel, she got more and more on my nerves as the book went on!) After being a pilot in the First World War, Larry returns home but is no longer interested in getting a job and settling down with Isabel. He says he wants to go to Europe and loaf around but he does work, down a coal mine, on farms and ships. He eventually travels to India searching for meaning in his life. In contrast there’s the other characters like Isabel who marries a stockbroker and her Uncle Elliot who is basically a snobby socialite living mostly in Paris. The story follows these characters through the next decade or so. It’s amusing, thoughtful and I liked it a lot.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3366736174013211069" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

